Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.20,0:00:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It started moving since the scattered Numbers cards were brought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.08,0:00:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This giant puzzle...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.61,0:00:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The number is the same as my scattered memories, 99 pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.02,0:00:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This structure... Is it some kind of message?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why would something like this be in Yuma's key...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.46,0:00:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.62,0:00:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My loss of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.36,0:00:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does it mean someone predicted this would happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.58,0:00:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.08,0:00:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Late, late!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.20,0:00:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really late!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.22,0:00:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful! Didn't you see the lights...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.54,0:01:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark... where's he going anyways?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.52,0:01:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me have a look at your deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.65,0:01:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.80,0:01:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.17,0:01:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.04,0:01:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.44,0:01:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean your Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.54,0:01:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are those cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.22,0:01:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those? They don't show up in my deck unless that guy is around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.70,0:01:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.89,0:01:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.41,0:01:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about the Dueling spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.54,0:01:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.74,0:01:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, to summarize...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.74,0:01:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have the Numbers cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then right now, you're just a terrible Duelist, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.91,0:01:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.74,0:01:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that mean all my victories so far
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.97,0:02:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were all relying on the strength of Numbers and that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.73,0:02:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.42,0:02:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without them, there's no way you can win against Shark and Tokunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.50,0:02:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.74,0:02:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't get the awesome power of my "bring it on"!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Duel Sphinx goes up dramatically, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sphinx"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.21,0:02:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to say "tactics".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.51,0:02:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.51,0:02:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuo-{\i1}kun{\i0} must be Yuma’s human translator!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.67,0:02:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, can you prove that you are still strong even without Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.57,0:02:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll Duel with Shark one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.91,0:02:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I can defeat him without Numbers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.90,0:02:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.91,0:02:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.19,0:02:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.56,0:02:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, I'll get to recognize your strength too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.71,0:02:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.13,0:02:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry up and go to Shark's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.24,0:02:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.59,0:02:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that guy hasn’t come to school recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:02:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After losing that Duel with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.68,0:02:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark’s reputation fell dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.71,0:03:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor says, he started hanging out with some bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.78,0:03:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.95,0:03:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.36,0:03:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.14,0:03:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.54,0:03:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.75,0:03:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.55,0:03:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.59,0:03:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.63,0:04:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.30,0:04:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.35,0:04:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.52,0:04:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma challenges Shark once again!\NCan he win without borrowing the power of Hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.63,0:04:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(280,491)}"Numbers 10:\N Shark’s Counterattack!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.01,0:04:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, those guys don’t understand at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.82,0:04:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm way stronger than before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you heading to, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.08,0:05:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, coming out at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.98,0:05:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all your fault, for making things so troublesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will Duel with Shark again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.52,0:05:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That boy who used a Numbers, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.36,0:05:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Duel has nothing to do with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.93,0:05:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you getting involved would make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, you're really planning to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.34,0:05:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.03,0:05:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't go see Shark, we won't be able to Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark is here, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.11,0:05:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! This place doesn't look too good! Hey, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:05:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a strange place…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:05:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back home, okay...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.34,0:06:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.51,0:06:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell you doin' here, brats? This is {\i1}my{\i0} territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerk...! Take your hands off hi-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Le'go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This stubborn kid's got some guts, ain't he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whas' happenin', Boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what're these guys up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerks! I came here to Duel, so lem'me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.70,0:06:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.95,0:06:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a vast difference between your body structure and his.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.46,0:06:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You stay outta this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro, what should we do about these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we get rid of 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Release them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.97,0:06:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you happen to know these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:06:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.64,0:06:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then your lives are spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.03,0:07:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys don't belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Shark! I have something to do with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.74,0:07:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please Duel with me once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That I can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave up Dueling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intentions... of ever playing again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.01,0:07:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark sure has fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those brothers are punk Duelists.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They attend all kinds of tournaments and threaten people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.90,0:07:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s wrong, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.11,0:07:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he give up Dueling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.41,0:07:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, why would he give up Dueling…?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt that’s because of losing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why would losing to me make him give up Dueling?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something you can never get back after losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something you can’t get back once you lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, that Shark started acting bad when he participated in the National Duel Tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something happened to him then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.40,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy... He should love Dueling...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, where’s Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he went home in a hurry…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me that Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.25,0:08:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel with me! What’s so fun about hanging around those punks?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.76,0:08:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we Duel, I'll understand everything about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Duel with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave up Dueling! Quit bugging me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.35,0:09:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gonna bring it to 'em!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.26,0:09:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he finally gave up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel… with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.72,0:09:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why would you give up Dueling?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth is {\i1}wrong{\i0} with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.77,0:09:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so concerned about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... obviously because we're friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we Duel, we're no longer strangers to each other…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:09:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're {\i1}friends!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you feel the same way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you {\i1}serious{\i0} about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean it! If I win, you have to withdraw from that gang!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what do you plan to bet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.09,0:10:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...bet this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.51,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don’t you regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I plan to {\i1}really{\i0} make you lose your most precious something!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.03,0:10:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, are you sure you want to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said this Duel has nothing to do with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be using the Numbers during this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers can only be defeated by Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Shark no longer owns a Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.42,0:10:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.46,0:11:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I do such a lowly thing like using a Numbers against a guy who doesn't even have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.55,0:11:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I've gotten way more skilled than the last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can still win, even without your strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. I will carefully observe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't simply forget that I've lost to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Maybe deep inside my heart, I’ve been waiting for this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel Disk, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Gazer, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}AR Vision - Link established.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.74,0:11:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.17,0:11:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.23,0:11:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.47,0:11:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.84,0:11:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.45,0:12:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His uses many powerful monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With only Gogogo Golem...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.75,0:12:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.77,0:12:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't attack on the first turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.55,0:12:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My set card is Battle Break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.25,0:12:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This trap can destroy one of my opponent's attacking monster, and end the battle phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This way, he won't be able to attack so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.42,0:12:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.60,0:12:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.05,0:12:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Killer Frilled Shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killer Frilled Shark? 700 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.73,0:12:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next I special summon Shark Sucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.96,0:12:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When there is another fish-type monster on the field, I can special summon this card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.26,0:12:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two level 3 monsters..!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.59,0:12:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.91,0:13:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay my level 3 Shark Sucker and Killer Frilled Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With these two monsters, I construct the overlay network!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.06,0:13:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Submersible -- Aero Shark!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.72,0:13:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1900 Attack Points, higher than Gogogo Golem's..!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, I have a trap for stopping Shark's attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.84,0:13:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Aero Shark’s effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.30,0:13:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once per turn, by detaching one overlay unit, I can inflict 400 damage to my opponent for every card in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are four cards left in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, you'll take 1600 damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.60,0:13:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:14:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I activate quickplay spell, Cyclone from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.63,0:14:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cyclone can destroy one spell or trap card on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.17,0:14:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! My trap was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.03,0:14:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Aero Shark! Attack Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Eater!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.05,0:14:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face down. Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.20,0:14:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! With only a single turn, Yuma's life dropped to 2300..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.87,0:14:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark is impossibly strong after all..!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.49,0:14:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.45,0:14:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, what’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.11,0:14:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren’t you come here to defeat me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're here to beat my fallen self again, then make fun of me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.15,0:14:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.45,0:14:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm after...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.83,0:14:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I won't be able to anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I use the Numbers...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.79,0:14:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn..!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.21,0:14:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.15,0:14:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, this is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:15:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gagaga Magician's effect, once per turn, lets me change its level to anything between 1 to 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, I have Resurrection of the Dead in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.39,0:15:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way if I revive Gogogo Golem, I can summon Aspiring Emperor - Hope to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.99,0:15:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though, I promised to not use my Numbers during this duel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.26,0:15:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, bring it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Numbers, your trump!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.77,0:15:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is Shark talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only Numbers can defeat other Numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He should know that already!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, summon it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.93,0:15:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Numbers, did you really think you can beat me without it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.93,0:15:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I accepted your duel like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.22,0:15:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll only mean something if I defeat you while you used Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.14,0:15:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, Shark is unbelievably strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.40,0:15:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.96,0:16:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I want to defeat Shark here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.87,0:16:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you thinking of using the Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.67,0:16:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said if you use the Numbers in this duel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be acting shamelessly underhanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.04,0:16:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't object.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.04,0:16:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't afford to lose the Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.60,0:16:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way, for the sake of winning..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.66,0:16:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Is to use the Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.49,0:16:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This duel isn't about my pride!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.40,0:16:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to save Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.82,0:16:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a spell card, Monster Reborn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll revive Gogogo Golem from my graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.92,0:16:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay my Level 4 monsters, Gagaga Magician and Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With these two monsters, I construct the Overlay network!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:16:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Numbers 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.79,0:17:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.71,0:17:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma used Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.99,0:17:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he promised he wouldn't use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.62,0:17:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, Yuma's duels are still relying on the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.09,0:17:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally here! the Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.26,0:17:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Aero Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.45,0:17:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So naive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Killer Frilled Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing Killer Frilled Shark from play from the graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.57,0:17:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the opponent monster's attack is negated,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And its attack power is decreased by 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.22,0:17:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap activate, Fish Rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this card, when a fish type monster is removed from play,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.79,0:17:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can special summon one level 3 or lower fish type monster from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.17,0:18:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll summon Big Jaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.53,0:18:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Hope couldn't destroy Aero Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.04,0:18:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, you made a mistake because you're too eager to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.21,0:18:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Reborn can revive an opponent's monster as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.79,0:18:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you revived Killer Frilled Shark from Shark's graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activated Gagaga Magician's effect, then XYZ Summoned Leviath Dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killer Frilled Shark's effect wouldn't have activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.56,0:18:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, using Leviath Dragon's ability, you could have destroyed Aero Shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.19,0:18:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So noisy! Everything is still fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.83,0:18:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's attack power is 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.57,0:18:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a monster with higher ATK than Hope on Shark’s field.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.87,0:18:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end my turn like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.84,0:18:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.21,0:18:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.91,0:18:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Aero Shark's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once per turn, by detaching an overlay unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.88,0:19:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can inflict 400 damage to my opponent for every card in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two cards in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, you take 800 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.64,0:19:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I summon Skull Kraken!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's two level 3 monsters...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.61,0:19:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.07,0:19:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have a card that can destroy Hope, a Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.54,0:19:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay my Level 3 monsters, Skull Kraken and Big Jaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.88,0:19:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With these two monsters, I construct the Overlay network!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Black Ray Lancer!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.87,0:19:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This duel is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.28,0:19:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Black Ray Lancer's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching an overlay unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.10,0:19:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During this turn, the effect of one of my opponent’s monsters is negated!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.56,0:19:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.02,0:20:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope---!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Numbers cannot be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.49,0:20:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after all, it's merely a card effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the effect is gone, then it can be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.18,0:20:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.18,0:20:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers’ effects are negated?..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Black Ray Lancer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.73,0:20:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Spear!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope---!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.26,0:20:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope.. was defeated...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.16,0:20:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He discovered the Numbers' weakness..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aero Shark, direct attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Eater!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.19,0:20:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, it was a complete defeat..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.74,0:20:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.78,0:20:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.31,0:21:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after I used the Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.41,0:21:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was almost too easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.08,0:21:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost to a duelist like you, losing everything and such...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.97,0:21:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How laughable..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.44,0:21:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As promised, I'll be taking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.52,0:21:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's... because we're friends, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.05,0:21:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This kind of thing... it's not even worth destroying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.33,0:21:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.65,0:21:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! You don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.93,0:21:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm staying with them because I like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.93,0:21:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They gave me a place to stay, to someone\Nwith no place like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.05,0:21:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So don't get involved again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.56,0:21:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.46,0:22:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.70,0:22:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.07,0:22:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's this week's quiz!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.36,0:22:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which magic card can be activated on the opponent's turn?\NEquipment Magic? Or Quickplay Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.15,0:22:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.76,0:22:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanna watch TV when I get home.\N The recent anime are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.87,0:23:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, this test is hard. \NLanguage, Math and English are especially bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.37,0:23:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm only average at science and social studies.\N The only thing I'm good at is P.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.55,0:23:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Wait up, Baby!) For who's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.25,0:23:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Is that, Baby!) ...am I remembering...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.69,0:23:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Just hold on, Baby!) ...the answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.25,0:23:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(What are we!? Baby!) ...they wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.92,0:23:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I write the correct answer on this paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.66,0:23:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in one year, in ten years, will anything change?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.40,0:23:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world I drew in the corner of my dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.50,0:23:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}one day I will race through the open sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.28,0:23:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one can blame this heart of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.15,0:23:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing is really correct!
